'''Booton Piton''' was a short<ref name="SWI75" /> [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="AOTC" /> [[Gender/Legends|female]]<ref name="SWI75" /> with [[Color/Legends|light]] skin. During a [[Local day/Legends|night]]<ref name="AOTC" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC2">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> Piton walked in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="Complete Locations">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2005)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and turned around to watch the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell]]'s<ref name="AOTC" /> [[Koro-2 all-environment exodrive airspeeder|''Koro-2'' all-environment exodrive airspeeder]]<ref name="CCS">''[[Star Wars: Complete Cross-Sections]]''</ref> descend through the air. When the speeder crashed, Piton, with the<ref name="AOTC" /> [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] [[Nardi Shodu]],<ref name="DB">{{DB|character|nardishodu|Shodu, Nardi}}</ref> approached the crash site.<ref name="AOTC" />

Shortly after,<ref name="AOTC" /> Piton traveled on an errand to the<ref name="SWI75" /> [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]], a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> in the district with Shodu.<ref name="SWI75" /> They entered the club [[Limb/Legends|arm]] in arm just in front of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], who were there to [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|capture]] Wesell.<ref name="AOTC" /> Shodu and Piton then walked behind a<ref name="AOTC" /> [[Turbolift/Legends|turbolift]]<ref name="Complete Locations" /> in the club. During the visit,<ref name="AOTC" /> Piton wore a form-fitting hunters [[Clothing/Legends|cap]]<ref name="SWI75" /> and a gray coat.<ref name="AOTC" />

==Behind the scenes==
Booton Piton first appeared in [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] and in its [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (video game)|video game adaptation]].<ref name="AOTC" /><ref name="GBA">[[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (video game)|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' video game]]</ref> Both released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref><ref name="GBADate">{{WebCite|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2002/05/15/star-wars-episode-ii-attack-of-the-clones-3|text=Star Wars Episode II: Attack of the Clones (GBA)|author=[https://www.ign.com/person/craig-ign Craig Harris]|date=2002-05-15|archivedate=20160325105351}}</ref> The Outlander Club scenes including Piton, who was portrayed by an uncredited extra, were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> The extra playing Piton had to guide around the masked extra playing Shodu.<ref name="SWI75" /> Prior to the film's release, Dokes was first pictured in the documentary "[[Making Episode II Webdocs|A Twinkle Beyond Pluto]],"<ref name="ATBP">{{SW|url=video/a-twinkle-beyond-pluto|series=Making Episode II Webdocs|text=Part 5: A Twinkle Beyond Pluto}}</ref> released on [[July 31]], [[2001]].<ref name="ATBP Date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/me2/archive.html|text=''Making Episode II Webdocs'' archive}}</ref> Piton was first identified in the [[2003]] web article "[[Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases]]."<ref name="crc">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/bts/article/f20030502/index.html|text=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases|int=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases}}</ref>

